<FlowDocument xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation" TextAlignment="Justify"
    xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml">
 
<Paragraph Style="{DynamicResource HeaderParagraphStyle}">
This section contains samples that demonstrate various settings in a PDF document using Essential PDF.
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph>
Here is a list of samples with descriptions.
</Paragraph>
<List>
<ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Document Settings</Bold> - This sample demonstrates Essential PDF's support for setting document properties. It also explains how XMP properties can be set using Essential PDF.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Page Settings</Bold> - This sample demonstrates the support for setting page-oriented properties such as page size, orientation, viewer preference, page view mode, and page transition. It also explains how transparency can be set.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Headers and Footers</Bold> - This sample demonstrates how headers and footers with page numbers and images can be inserted using Essential PDF.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Layers</Bold> - This sample demonstrates how multiple layers can be added to a page and how elements are drawn over each layer.</Paragraph></ListItem>
</List>
</FlowDocument>
